Un fallo de los coches autónomos: las personas
<a href="https://goo.gl/photos/5e9EBL9p4yjAatdx5" title="Coche"><img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/pJge36Cwtdv6VNtnabkvqpEuVEUlqUK3zH2S1xhV34E482QFYabm3HPsQrSLvGBzxVWModmPMLjsNqITQHqYZa-LbzWD4mGGKWgmRaNO14A5oIxQ51K17k-bLPzC5LATq28y7tvFfbJINzxPsyLrMN0YTVD_ucAZAXu2slSy0SFl8CqNvrXbojtajCRHfqOy5Xhd8waG7IsVig49mkuPN3vGw7Ze6XPfVAwz79odxPGpZxyc1mBz7F2zDyyPGlVJQA6XYr2PpA_s4anirQo2Yog5Chta9hpBa-cGbVvYrOPYlIay8KxZoT07oOuXgkFiK0lq0OuxmM6dQj0t-eoKpC9sEFnuGALpbr7JKt60GiLvAJJCgHsroV_NmeYZLCXNmeDq84xPu08lHWRb76C-v7qyq5FQ1U9vC_7RapsHVFDRhMTECpZkXfwxJ4Was2WubiO_xqlzDTJ1mHght-VfqDjuEcKhcfeZlIPVBLYmIBa70qFkkqEsZW3IdslExJ-IDMfHM-lahjEOVld4Ev6TCvihxkHb05S8O9gjWDqIo-zl5rL1GJTOyo7UFYwYPvchL7f2=w823-h549-no" width="240"  alt="Coche" style="float:left; margin:5px"></a>
Mucho se está escribiendo en estos días sobre el coche autónomo, sus accidentes (o no) y me gustó leer <a href="http://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2015-12-18/humans-are-slamming-into-driverless-cars-and-exposing-a-key-flaw">Humans Are Slamming Into Driverless Cars and Exposing a Key Flaw</a> porque me recuerda lo difícil que es conducir cumpliendo las normas (incluso para humanos).

Sobre algunos golpes por detrás producidos por humanos agresivos o despistados, poco acostumbrados a conductores que respeten las normas: 

<blockquote>
Driverless vehicles have never been at fault, the study found: They're usually hit from behind in slow-speed crashes by inattentive or aggressive humans unaccustomed to machine motorists that always follow the rules and proceed with caution.
</blockquote>

A veces es peligroso ser demasiado cauteloso (¿Quién no ha visto alguna vez el lío que produce alguien que va despacio por una calle o carretera?):

<blockquote>
Ten days later, a Mountain View motorcycle cop noticed traffic stacking up
behind a Google car going 24 miles an hour in a busy 35 mph zone. 

[...]

"I like it when people err on the side of caution. But can something be too cautious? Yeah."
</blockquote>

Pero, claro, ¿nos atreveríamos a programar una máquina para saltarse la ley? Aunque sólo fuera un poquito, ¿Cuánto de poquito?

<blockquote>
One approach is to teach the vehicles when it's OK to break the rules, such as crossing a double yellow line to avoid a bicyclist or road workers.

"It's a sticky area," Schoettle said. "If you program them to not follow the law, how much do you let them break the law?"
</blockquote>


Nos esperan tiempos interesantes.

